<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued January 12 at 10:18PM EST until January 13 at 7:00PM EST by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM EST
SATURDAY...
* WHAT... High wind, snow, and blowing snow. Additional
accumulation localized up to 3 inches and wind gusts near 50 mph
through Saturday.
* WHERE...St. Clair, Macomb, Wayne, Lenawee and Monroe Counties.
* WHEN...Until 7 PM EST Saturday.
* IMPACTS... Plan on hazardous road conditions. Widespread blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. Gusty winds could
bring down tree branches resulting in power outages.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... Scattered snow showers return as very
strong wind develops late tonight through Saturday with gusts
near 50 mph. Arctic air surging into the region leads to
temperatures falling well below freezing and icy surfaces on
untreated roads.</description>
<instruction>Slow down and use caution while traveling.</instruction>
